1. Moramo da imamo strogu *kontrolu* u našoj fabrici da bismo se uverili da se pridržavamo propisa. (We need to have strict *control* in our factory to make sure we comply with regulations.)
2. Inspektor je obavio *kontrolu* kvaliteta proizvoda pre nego što su pušteni u prodaju. (The inspector conducted a quality *control* check of the products before they were released for sale.)
3. Vlasnik restorana je uveo sistem *kontrole* količine hrane koju serviraju gostima. (The restaurant owner implemented a system for *controlling* the amount of food they serve to guests.)
4. Zaposleni na aerodromu su bili podvrgnuti detaljnoj *kontroli* pre ukrcavanja na avion. (Airport employees underwent a thorough *check* before boarding the plane.)
5. Nastavnici su bili odgovorni za *kontrolu* testova koji su se nalazili na njihovim stolovima. (Teachers were responsible for *checking* the tests that were on their desks.)
6. Kompanija je uspela da ostvari bolju *kontrolu* nad svojim finansijama nakon što je unajmila stručnjaka za računovodstvo. (The company was able to achieve better *financial control* after hiring an accounting expert.)
7. Kada je primetio da ga deca gledaju, otac je brzo preuzeo *kontrolu* nad automobilom i uspeo da izbegne sudar. (When he noticed that his children were watching, the father quickly took *control* of the car and managed to avoid a collision.)
8. Ministarstvo je objavilo novi zakon o *kontroli* širenja koronavirusa u javnim prostorima. (The Ministry announced a new law on *controlling* the spread of the coronavirus in public spaces.)